This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   The user issued a single agent directive: "Agent A: spec/prompts/wave-02/WP-V2-02-wall-depth.md → branch feat/wp-v2-02-wall-depth" — implement WP-V2-02 covering:
   - Gap 1: Location line geometry offset in 3D (`makeWallMesh`) and plan wire (`planWallMesh`) — shift mesh perpendicular to wall axis based on `locationLine` property
   - Gap 2: Wall Joins modify tool (`'wall-join'`) with state machine (idle→selected, N=cycle miter/butt/square, Enter=accept→console.warn stub, Esc=cancel)
   - Gap 3: `baseConstraintOffsetMm` raises wall base Y; `topConstraintLevelId` resolves wall height from level elevation + `topConstraintOffsetMm`
   All changes on branch `feat/wp-v2-02-wall-depth`, `make verify` must pass.

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - React 19 + Vite + TypeScript, Tailwind, Zustand, Three.js stack in pnpm monorepo
   - `packages/core` — pure data types (`Element` union, `WallLocationLine`)
   - `packages/ui` — icon registry (`Icons`, `IconName`, `IconLabels`)
   - `packages/web` — main app: viewport (Three.js), plan canvas, tools, state
   - `WallLocationLine` type: `wall-centerline | finish-face-exterior | finish-face-interior | core-centerline | core-face-exterior | core-face-interior`
